HEADWORD: Oxanilic
<hw>Ox`an*il"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ox</ets>alic
+ <ets>anil</ets>ine.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or
derived from, oxalic acid and aniline; -- used to designate an acid
obtained in white crystalline scales by heating these substances
together.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oxanilide</ent>⟦br⟧
